    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1715"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 834.001 Sch 1/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Minister for Foreign Affairs</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 17th of August last, enclosing a letter, with office
                    copy, addressed to the President of the United States by His Excellency Señor
                    Don Eduardo Schaerer, announcing his elevation to the Chief Magistracy of
                    Paraguay.</p>
                <p>His Excellency’s letter has been laid before the President, whose reply will be
                    delivered to its high destination through the American Legation at
                    Montevideo.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
